The Second Iteration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recall: 
\begin_inset Formula $Pr[\lnot S_{1}\cap\lnot S_{2}]=Pr[\lnot S_{2}|\lnot S_{1}]\cdot Pr[\lnot S_{1}]$
\end_inset

 probability we don't screw up in first and second iteration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $Pr[\lnot S_{2}|\lnot S_{1}]=1-\frac{k}{\text{\# of remaining edges}}$
\end_inset

 probability we not screw up in second iteration given that we didn't do
 it already.
\end_layout

