\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 vertices.
 By the Contraction Algorithm analysis (without repeated trials):
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Pr[output=(A_{i},B_{i})]\ge\frac{2}{n(n-1)}=\frac{1}{{n \choose 2}}\qquad\forall_{i=1,2,\dots,t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $t=$
\end_inset

the number of different min-cuts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\bar under
Note
\bar default
: 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{i}$
\end_inset

's are 
\bar under
disjoint
\bar default
 events (i.e.
 only one can happen) 
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow$
\end_inset

their probabilities sum to at most 1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\bar under
Thus
\bar default
: 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{t}{{n \choose 2}}\le1\Rightarrow t\le{n \choose 2}$
\end_inset


